{"timestamp":"2026-05-05T16:25:26.328Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"exec_command_end","call_id":"call_NCPoSqJ4Sr2qMz7o8IN0zu8j","process_id":"49225","turn_id":"019df8f4-eac0-7653-b4eb-fc3191c2195c","command":["/bin/zsh","-lc","nl -ba README.md | sed -n '1,260p'"],"cwd":"/Users/rizel/Documents/work/skills","parsed_cmd":[{"type":"read","cmd":"nl -ba README.md | sed -n '1,260p'","name":"README.md","path":"README.md"}],"source":"unified_exec_startup","stdout":"","stderr":"","aggregated_output":"     1\t![Entire Skills cover](assets/gh-repo-cover.png)\n     2\t\n     3\t# Skills\n     4\t\n     5\tCross-agent skills and commands powered by Entire.\n     6\t\n     7\t## Skills\n     8\t\n     9\t### `session-handoff`\n    10\t\n    11\tReads Entire session metadata and helps move work from one agent to another without making the user reconstruct the context manually.\n    12\t\n    13\tCurrent behavior:\n    14\t\n    15\t- auto-detects the most recent session from `.git/entire-sessions/`\n    16\t- reads the raw transcript at the path stored in session metadata\n    17\t- produces a structured compaction summary (Task Overview, Current State, Important Discoveries, Next Steps, Context to Preserve) instead of dumping raw transcript lines\n    18\t- surfaces unanswered questions from the previous agent for the user to answer\n    19\t- supports checkpoint handoff via `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n    20\t- falls back to `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --raw-transcript --no-pager` if full output is unavailable\n    21\t- resolves checkpoints from: local `entire/checkpoints/v1` branch, `.entire/settings.json` `checkpoint_remote`, or nearby local clone\n    22\t- filters sessions by agent name (e.g. \"codex\", \"gemini\") when mentioned\n    23\t\n    24\t### `session-to-skill`\n    25\t\n    26\tTurns Entire session history into a focused reusable skill draft without making the user manually find, paste, or reconstruct old agent conversations.\n    27\t\n    28\tCurrent behavior:\n    29\t\n    30\t- asks what reusable behavior the user wants to extract before reading transcripts\n    31\t- accepts an explicit session ID or checkpoint ID when the user already has one\n    32\t- searches Entire history with `entire search \"<query>\" --json` when the user describes a repeated workflow\n    33\t- expands selected checkpoints with `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n    34\t- reads active session metadata from `.git/entire-sessions/<session-id>.json` when needed\n    35\t- extracts durable lessons such as repo conventions, validation commands, user corrections, required inputs, and behaviors to avoid\n    36\t- drafts a focused `SKILL.md` instead of recapping the whole session\n    37\t- asks before writing, installing, or overwriting a skill\n    38\t\n    39\t### `explain`\n    40\t\n    41\tTraces source code back to the original conversation where it was created. Use `/explain` with a function, file, or line of code to understand _why_ it exists.\n    42\t\n    43\tCurrent behavior:\n    44\t\n    45\t- identifies the commit that introduced the code via git blame/log\n    46\t- reads the session transcript via `entire explain --no-pager --commit <sha>`\n    47\t- works with functions, files, and individual line changes\n    48\t- reports clearly when code is untracked, uncommitted, or created outside an Entire session\n    49\t\n    50\t### `what-happened`\n    51\t\n    52\tExplains what happened to a specific code block by tracing the latest change for a file line,\n    53\trange, or pasted snippet through git blame and Entire checkpoints.\n    54\t\n    55\tCurrent behavior:\n    56\t\n    57\t- resolves file lines, ranges, or pasted snippets to exact line numbers\n    58\t- asks for a concrete file line, range, or snippet before running provenance commands\n    59\t- deduplicates commit and checkpoint lookups before running expensive transcript commands\n    60\t- asks before expanding broad ranges with many unique commits\n    61\t- summarizes `entire explain` output without dumping raw transcripts by default; raw transcript expansion is opt-in\n    62\t- falls back to clearly labeled current-code analysis when checkpoint-backed context is unavailable\n    63\t\n    64\tExamples:\n    65\t\n    66\t- \"tell me why this code is like that\"\n    67\t- \"why does this code look like this?\"\n    68\t- \"what happened here: `src/auth.ts:42-57`\"\n    69\t- \"what happened at `src/auth.ts:42`\"\n    70\t- \"what happened to this block?\" plus a pasted snippet\n    71\t\n    72\t### `search`\n    73\t\n    74\tSearches Entire checkpoint history and transcripts to find prior work by topic, repo, branch, author, or time window.\n    75\t\n    76\tCurrent behavior:\n    77\t\n    78\t- runs `entire search \"<query>\" --json` and summarizes the top matches\n    79\t- supports filters: `--repo`, `--branch`, `--author`, `--date`, and inline query filters like `author:<name>`, `date:week`\n    80\t- drills into a specific result with `entire explain --checkpoint <id> --full --no-pager`\n    81\t- broadens searches progressively when initial results are empty (remove branch filter, widen date, simplify terms)\n    82\t\n    83\t## Installation\n    84\t\n    85\tInstall with [skills](https://skills.sh/) CLI (universal, works with any [Agent Skills](https://agentskills.io)-compatible tool):\n    86\t\n    87\t```bash\n    88\tnpx skills add https://github.com/entireio/skills --all\n    89\t# or a single skill:\n    90\tnpx skills add https://github.com/entireio/skills --skill session-handoff\n    91\t```\n    92\t\n    93\t<!-- prettier-ignore-start -->\n    94\t\n    95\t<details>\n    96\t<summary>Claude Code</summary>\n    97\t\n    98\t```bash\n    99\t/plugin marketplace add entireio/skills\n   100\t/plugin install entire\n   101\t```\n   102\t\n   103\t</details>\n   104\t\n   105\t<details>\n   106\t<summary>Cursor</summary>\n   107\t\n   108\tC