{"timestamp":"2026-05-05T16:26:05.817Z","type":"event_msg","payload":{"type":"exec_command_end","call_id":"call_D83ImB3dVbGWXkaGArYQ112l","process_id":"41485","turn_id":"019df8f4-eac0-7653-b4eb-fc3191c2195c","command":["/bin/zsh","-lc","nl -ba README.md | sed -n '1,240p'"],"cwd":"/Users/rizel/Documents/work/skills","parsed_cmd":[{"type":"read","cmd":"nl -ba README.md | sed -n '1,240p'","name":"README.md","path":"README.md"}],"source":"unified_exec_startup","stdout":"","stderr":"","aggregated_output":"     1\t![Entire Skills cover](assets/gh-repo-cover.png)\n     2\t\n     3\t# Entire Skills\n     4\t\n     5\tBring your Entire context to your agents with reusable skills.\n     6\t\n     7\tThe [Entire CLI](https://github.com/entireio/cli) captures the context behind your\n     8\tcode changes: prompts, transcripts, checkpoints, and the decisions that led to\n     9\teach change, alongside your git history. This repository packages agent-invokable\n    10\tworkflows that teach coding agents how to use that context.\n    11\t\n    12\tInstead of looking up Entire commands yourself, you can ask in plain language and\n    13\tlet your agent search prior work, inspect provenance, hand off session state, or\n    14\tturn repeated workflows into new skills.\n    15\t\n    16\t## Install\n    17\t\n    18\tInstall every skill with the [skills](https://skills.sh/) CLI:\n    19\t\n    20\t```bash\n    21\tnpx skills add https://github.com/entireio/skills --all\n    22\t```\n    23\t\n    24\tInstall one skill:\n    25\t\n    26\t```bash\n    27\tnpx skills add https://github.com/entireio/skills --skill search\n    28\t```\n    29\t\n    30\tSee [Agent-Specific Installation](#agent-specific-installation) for Claude Code,\n    31\tCodex, Cursor, Copilot, Gemini CLI, OpenCode, and Antigravity.\n    32\t\n    33\t## Quick Start\n    34\t\n    35\tAfter installing, ask your agent for the workflow you want:\n    36\t\n    37\t```text\n    38\tsearch past work for rate limiting\n    39\t```\n    40\t\n    41\t```text\n    42\t/explain src/auth.ts\n    43\t```\n    44\t\n    45\t```text\n    46\twhat happened here: src/auth.ts:42-57\n    47\t```\n    48\t\n    49\t```text\n    50\thand off this session\n    51\t```\n    52\t\n    53\t```text\n    54\tturn my release notes workflow into a skill\n    55\t```\n    56\t\n    57\tFor a guided walkthrough, see the\n    58\t[Entire Skills tutorial](https://docs.entire.io/skills/tutorial).\n    59\t\n    60\t## Cross-Agent by Design\n    61\t\n    62\tSkills are plain, portable instructions that can be installed across\n    63\t[Agent Skills](https://agentskills.io)-compatible tools. This repo includes\n    64\tmetadata and shims for multiple agents so the same Entire workflows can follow\n    65\tyou across development environments.\n    66\t\n    67\t## What These Skills Help Agents Do\n    68\t\n    69\t| Goal | Example prompt |\n    70\t| --- | --- |\n    71\t| Find prior work before making changes | `search past work for the migration` |\n    72\t| Explain why code exists | `/explain parseConfig` |\n    73\t| Investigate a confusing code block | `what happened at src/auth.ts:42` |\n    74\t| Pick up another agent's work | `hand off the codex session` |\n    75\t| Convert repeated work into a reusable workflow | `make a skill from this session` |\n    76\t\n    77\t## Included Skills\n    78\t\n    79\tThe current repository includes these skills. Each skill lives in\n    80\t`skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`.\n    81\t\n    82\t### `search`\n    83\t\n    84\tFinds prior work in your Entire history by topic, repo, branch, author, or time\n    85\twindow, so your agent can bring past context into the current task before making\n    86\tchanges.\n    87\t\n    88\t### `explain`\n    89\t\n    90\tTraces a function, file, or line back to the session that created it, so your\n    91\tagent can answer the intent behind code instead of only describing what the code\n    92\tcurrently does.\n    93\t\n    94\t### `what-happened`\n    95\t\n    96\tCombines git history with Entire checkpoint context to explain why a specific\n    97\tblock of code looks the way it does. Useful during code review, debugging, or\n    98\tregression investigation.\n    99\t\n   100\t### `session-handoff`\n   101\t\n   102\tReads saved or active session context so another agent can pick up the task\n   103\tstate, important discoveries, blockers, and next steps without making you\n   104\treconstruct everything manually.\n   105\t\n   106\t### `session-to-skill`\n   107\t\n   108\tTurns repeated agent sessions into reusable `SKILL.md` drafts. It extracts the\n   109\tprocess from real work instead of asking you to write idealized instructions\n   110\tfrom scratch.\n   111\t\n   112\t## Requirements\n   113\t\n   114\tThese skills are designed for repositories where Entire has captured useful\n   115\thistory. Some workflows need:\n   116\t\n   117\t- the [Entire CLI](https://github.com/entireio/cli) installed\n   118\t- a git repository with Entire sessions, checkpoints, or checkpoint-backed commits\n   119\t- `entire login` for workflows that use the Entire search service\n   120\t- a GitHub `origin` and pushed, indexed checkpoints for remote search results\n   121\t\n   122\tIndividual skills handle missing context differently and should explain what is\n   123\tmissing before falling back or stopping.\n   124\t\n   125\t## Agent-Specific Installation\n   126\t\n   127\t<!-- prettier-ignore-start -->\n   128\t\n   129\t<details>\n   130\t<summary>Claude Code</summary>\n   131\t\n   132\t```bash\n   133\t/plugin marketplace add entireio/skills\n   134\t/plugin install entire\n   135\t```\n   136\t\n   137\t</details>\n   138\t\n   139\t<details>\n   140\t<summary>Codex (OpenAI)</summary>\n   141\t\n   142\tClone into the cross-client discovery path:\n   143\t\n   144\t```bash\n   145\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.agents/skills/entire\n   146\t```\n   147\t\n   148\tCodex auto-discovers skills from `~/.agents/skills/` and `.agents/skills/`.\n   149\tUpdate with:\n   150\t\n   151\t```bash\n   152\tcd ~/.agents/skills/entire && git pull\n   153\t```\n   154\t\n   155\t</details>\n   156\t\n   157\t<details>\n   158\t<summary>Cursor</summary>\n   159\t\n   160\tCopy skills into the cross-client discovery directory:\n   161\t\n   162\t```bash\n   163\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.cursor/skills/entire\n   164\t```\n   165\t\n   166\tCursor auto-discovers skills from `.agents/skills/` and `.cursor/skills/`.\n   167\t\n   168\t</details>\n   169\t\n   170\t<details>\n   171\t<summary>Copilot</summary>\n   172\t\n   173\t```bash\n   174\t/plugin install https://github.com/entireio/skills\n   175\t# or\n   176\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.copilot/skills/entire\n   177\t```\n   178\t\n   179\tCopilot auto-discovers skills from `.copilot/skills/`.\n   180\t\n   181\t</details>\n   182\t\n   183\t<details>\n   184\t<summary>Gemini CLI</summary>\n   185\t\n   186\t```bash\n   187\tgemini extensions install https://github.com/entireio/skills\n   188\t```\n   189\t\n   190\tUpdate with:\n   191\t\n   192\t```bash\n   193\tgemini extensions update entire\n   194\t```\n   195\t\n   196\t</details>\n   197\t\n   198\t<details>\n   199\t<summary>OpenCode</summary>\n   200\t\n   201\tCopy skills into the cross-client discovery directory:\n   202\t\n   203\t```bash\n   204\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.agents/skills/entire\n   205\t```\n   206\t\n   207\tOpenCode auto-discovers skills from `.agents/skills/`, `.opencode/skills/`, and\n   208\t`.claude/skills/`.\n   209\t\n   210\t</details>\n   211\t\n   212\t<details>\n   213\t<summary>Antigravity</summary>\n   214\t\n   215\tClone into the Antigravity skills directory:\n   216\t\n   217\t```bash\n   218\tgit clone https://github.com/entireio/skills.git ~/.antigravity/skills/entire\n   219\t```\n   220\t\n   221\tUpdate with:\n   222\t\n   223\t```bash\n   224\tcd ~/.antigravity/skills/entire && git pull\n   225\t```\n   226\t\n   227\t</details>\n   228\t\n   229\t<!-- prettier-ignore-end -->\n   230\t\n   231\t## Contributing\n   232\t\n   233\tSee [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md) for local development, validation, and pull\n   234\trequest guidance.\n   235\t\n   236\t## License\n   237\t\n   238\tThis project is licensed under the terms in [LICENSE](LICENSE).\n","exit_code":0,"duration":{"secs":0,"nanos":8459},"formatted_output":"","status":"completed"}}
